 Transformative social innovation: a sustainability transitions perspective on social innovation
@inproceedings{Haxeltine2013TransformativeSI, title={Transformative social innovation: a sustainability transitions perspective on social innovation}, author={A Haxeltine and F Avelino and J Wittmayer and R Kemp and P Weaver and J Backhaus and T O'Riordan}, year={2013} }
Solutions to the grand societal challenges faced by the knowledge society of the early 21st century will necessarily involve systemic change. This in turn implies a need to understand the ways in which social innovation can be ultimately transformative (creating the conditions for systemic change).

